cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.MS, cs.NA

Reasoning: 
- cs.AR (Architecture): The paper focuses on understanding the scalability of a specific hardware architecture, Phytium FT-2000+, and how it affects the performance of SpMV. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper aims to develop a performance analytical model to better understand the factors that affect the scalability of SpMV on Phytium FT-2000+. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper deals with parallel programming and the challenges of achieving linear speedup on many-core architectures. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper focuses on SpMV, which is a common operation in scientific and HPC applications that involves mathematical computations. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the empirical evaluation of over 1000 SpMV datasets and the development of a performance analytical model, which are both related to numerical analysis.
